HEADWORD: Idoneous
<hw>I*do"ne*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>idoneus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Appropriate; suitable; proper; fit;
adequate.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An ecclesiastical benefice . . . ought to be conferred on an
<qex>idoneous</qex> person.</q> <rj><qau>Ayliffe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idorgan</ent>⟦br⟧
